video_info.description:
NEET 2025 Big Update by NTA!😱

The NTA has introduced major changes for NEET 2025. Aadhaar authentication is now mandatory for Indian and NRI applicants, with strict ID verification at exam centers. The exam will be held on May 4, 2025, in offline mode with a revised pattern of 180 compulsory questions in 3 hours, removing optional questions. 

The official site has shifted to neet.nta.nic.in, and candidates can now choose three exam cities. The tie-breaking policy includes a random selection step if needed. Ensure Aadhaar details and mobile numbers are updated to avoid issues.
